========================================================================
SCIENTIFIC INTERPRETATION
========================================================================

  HORUS v3 attractors (A1–A4) are OBSERVER-FRAME ARTIFACTS.

  They are stable ONLY in the specific coordinate system defined
  by the standard E-field extraction: result[11:6].

  Destroy that coordinate system (via desync, popcount, lag, or
  rotation) and the attractor labels change — sometimes dramatically.

  This does NOT invalidate the COMPUTATION — `computed` is still
  fully deterministic and produces consistent arithmetic results.
  What is invalidated is the CLAIM that A1–A4 are intrinsic
  dynamical invariants independent of observation frame.

  The correct characterization of HORUS v3 after C23:
    • Arithmetic: invariant, frame-independent (proved C18–C22)
    • Attractors: observer-defined, frame-dependent (proved C23)
    • Causal closure: holds for arithmetic (proved C18–C22)
    • Attractor labels: NOT causally invariant under coord change

